The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Very special, says Gronkjaer
Braga, June 19 (Reuters): Eight days after the death of his mother, Jesper Gronkjaer struck a very, very special goal for Denmark in their 2-0 defeat of Bulgaria at the European Championship Friday (as reported in Saturdays Late City edition). The 26-year-old said the goal had been very special for my country, Denmark, and very, very special for me, for personal reasons. Gronkjaer arrived in Portugal only three days ago after burying his mother.  Copyright 
